title: Mallacoota East Of The Lake Plants

items.title: Plantae spp.
items.content_text: Closest I can think of is Ricinocarpus pinifolius but greyish foliage doesn't fit.

items.title: Paracaleana minor
items.content_text: Growing in centre of Barracoota Track, not far from Caleana major. Location approximate.

items.title: Hakea decurrens subsp. platytaenia
items.content_text: Not sure of ID. Fruit appears very wide compared to typical subsp. physocarpa. Location approximate.

items.title: Xyris operculata
items.content_text: I returned to this spot on Jan 23 2014 and obtained pic3 which is the ID feature (bracts in many rows, large at the top and getting progressively smaller to the bottom). Plants about 50cm tall growing in a short sandy section of the track.

items.title: Hibbertia riparia
items.content_text: Not sure of ID. Leaves look long for H. riparia but nothing else seems to fit? Location approximate.

items.title: Dianella aff. caerulea (Mallacoota)
items.content_text: Tall, lanky with aerial shoots. Location approximate.

items.title: Lepidosperma concavum
items.content_text: Not sure of ID. Narrow culms, shorter than or equal to leaf length.
